snippet.textDisplay: Whatever Nizam ud Din Torwali is selling, I am sold!   I want it!   Ooooo Bhaaiiiee, khoobsoorti ki bhi koie hadd hoti hy . . . itni pyari zaban . . . must know what he is saying; need to know what he is saying -- why caint I get the English subtitles!  Plus, I find Noorima Rehan and Zeb Bangash have made the song Sur-real!  Is Mahmaan a song or a meditation . . .  great choice of artists and arrangement.  Mairi nazar main yay aik maddhosh kernay wala gana hy--is ki sublime dhun nay mairay hosh urah diay hain. 🥰 BTW, is Swati culture Pashawar Patthan culture?  Why are we not taught about the wonderous diversity of Pakistan in our schools!?!   Maybe we need a multi-language course, in schools, where we get an introduction to the languages of different provinces.  Imagine if every Pakistani, in addition to Urdu and English, at least spoke basic Punjabi, Sindhi, Baluchi . . . .   I wanna be part of that inclusive world of diverse Pakistan; for the moment I can access it at Coke Studio Pakistan.  Thank-you Coke Studio Pakistan for giving me the different parts of myself; yay sab hamara culture hy aur hamari heritage bhi.  Coke Studio Pakistan Zindabad!
